Sentencas: The samarium doped ceria-carbonate (SDC/Na2CO3) nanocomposite systems have shown to be excellent electrolyte materials for low-temperature SOFCs, yet, the conduction mechanism is not well understood.
Titulo: Ceria-based nanocomposite with simultaneous proton and oxygen ion conductivity for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, a four-probe d.c. technique has been successfully employed to study the conduction behavior of proton and oxygen ion in SDC/Na2CO3 nanocomposite electrolyte.
Titulo: Ceria-based nanocomposite with simultaneous proton and oxygen ion conductivity for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results demonstrated that the SDC/Na2CO3 nanocomposite electrolyte possesses unique simultaneous proton and oxygen ion conduction property, with the proton conductivity 1-2 orders of magnitude higher than the oxygen ion conductivity in the temperature range of 200-600 degrees C, indicating the proton conduction in the nanocomposite mainly accounts for the enhanced total ionic conductivity.
Titulo: Ceria-based nanocomposite with simultaneous proton and oxygen ion conductivity for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is suggested that the interface in composite electrolyte supplies high conductive path for proton, while oxygen ions are probably transported by the SDC grain interiors.
Titulo: Ceria-based nanocomposite with simultaneous proton and oxygen ion conductivity for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An empirical Swing Model has been proposed as a possible mechanism of superior proton conduction.
Titulo: Ceria-based nanocomposite with simultaneous proton and oxygen ion conductivity for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
